{"title": "Devotional Hours with the Bible, Vol 2", "description": "One way of studying the Bible is to get from it practical lessons from our daily life. This is the purpose that is in mind in this book. It does not attempt to cover every chapter; to do this would make it altogether too long--it deals only with what appear to be leading and representative portions of the Bible.\r\n\r\nIt is a book for use in the inner chamber where life receives its impulses for conduct, for duty, for service, and for devotion. The Bible is a very ancient book, but it is also a book for to-day. It brings us face to face with God, and its teachings are meant to guide us in all our ways. (adapted from the Preface)\r\n\r\nThis is volume 2 of 8 and is subtitled \"From the Crossing of the Red Sea to the Close of David's Life\".\r\n\r\n<strong>Books in this series:</strong><br>\r\n<a href=\"https://librivox.org/devotional-hours-with-the-bible-vol-1-by-j-r-miller/\">Volume 1: From the Creation to the Crossing of the Red Sea</a><br>\r\n<a href=\"https://librivox.org/devotional-hours-with-the-bible-vol-2-by-j-r-miller/\">Volume 2: From the Crossing of the Red Sea to the Close of David's Life</a><br>\r\nVolume 3: The Gospel by Matthew\r\nVolume 4: Solomon to Malachi\r\nVolume 5: Readings in the Synoptic Gospels on the Life of Christ\r\nVolume 6: Readings from the Psalms\r\nVolume 7: The Gospel of St. John\r\nVolume 8: Readings in the Acts, the Epistles and Revelation", "duration": 26534, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18583", "name": "James Russell Miller"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/devotionalhours2_2502_librivox/devotionalhours2_2502.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Christianity - Commentary"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "KevinS"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [